BA May Fly Business Class to Boston, Washington, Telegraph Says

-- B y   T i m   B a r w e l l
-- 
2011-09-25T15:05:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/ba-may-fly-business-class-to-boston-washington-telegraph-says.html
British Airways Plc is considering
operating business class only flights to  Boston  and  Washington 
after its New York service remained resilient, the Sunday
Telegraph reported, citing an interview with Chief Executive
Officer Keith Williams.  BA has a load factor of about 70 percent on its London City
to New York business-class service, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Barwell in London on 
 tbarwell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Ludden at 
 jludden@bloomberg.net  